propertyDescriptor.name: Path Filter
propertyDescriptor.description: When Recurse Subdirectories is true, then only subdirectories whose path matches the given regular expression will be scanned

propertyDescriptor.name: Batch Size
propertyDescriptor.description: The maximum number of files to pull in each iteration

propertyDescriptor.name: Keep Source File
propertyDescriptor.description: If true, the file is not deleted after it has been copied to the Content Repository; this causes the file to be picked up continually and is useful for testing purposes.  If not keeping original NiFi will need write permissions on the directory it is pulling from otherwise it will ignore the file.

propertyDescriptor.name: Recurse Subdirectories
propertyDescriptor.description: Indicates whether or not to pull files from subdirectories

propertyDescriptor.name: Polling Interval
propertyDescriptor.description: Indicates how long to wait before performing a directory listing

propertyDescriptor.name: Ignore Hidden Files
propertyDescriptor.description: Indicates whether or not hidden files should be ignored

propertyDescriptor.name: Minimum File Age
propertyDescriptor.description: The minimum age that a file must be in order to be pulled; any file younger than this amount of time (according to last modification date) will be ignored

propertyDescriptor.name: Maximum File Age
propertyDescriptor.description: The maximum age that a file must be in order to be pulled; any file older than this amount of time (according to last modification date) will be ignored

propertyDescriptor.name: Minimum File Size
propertyDescriptor.description: The minimum size that a file must be in order to be pulled

propertyDescriptor.name: Maximum File Size
propertyDescriptor.description: The maximum size that a file can be in order to be pulled

propertyDescriptor.name: Source Table
propertyDescriptor.description: Name of table including schema (if applicable)

propertyDescriptor.name: Source Fields
propertyDescriptor.description: Field names (in order) to read from the source table. ie. the select fields. The format is separated by newline. Inconsistent order will cause corruption of the downstream Hive data.

propertyDescriptor.name: Load Strategy
propertyDescriptor.description: Whether to load the entire table or perform an incremental extract

propertyDescriptor.name: High-Water Mark Property Name
propertyDescriptor.description: Name of the flow file attribute that should contain the current hig-water mark date, and which this processor will update with new values.  Required if the load strategy is set to INCREMENTAL.

allProperties.nameKey: NiFi Flow-Fetch RDBMS Data-High-Water Mark Property Name

propertyDescriptor.name: Date Field
propertyDescriptor.description: Source field containing a modified date for tracking incremental load

propertyDescriptor.name: Overlap Period
propertyDescriptor.description: Amount of time to overlap into the last load date to ensure long running transactions missed by previous load weren't missed. Recommended: >0s

propertyDescriptor.name: Max Wait Time
propertyDescriptor.description: The maximum amount of time allowed for a running SQL select query  , zero means there is no limit. Max time less than 1 second will be equal to zero.

allProperties.nameKey: NiFi Flow-Fetch RDBMS Data-Max Wait Time

propertyDescriptor.name: Backoff Period
propertyDescriptor.description: Only records older than the backoff period will be eligible for pickup. This can be used in the ILM use case to define a retention period. Recommended: >5m

propertyDescriptor.name: Minimum Time Unit
propertyDescriptor.description: The minimum unit of data eligible to load. For the ILM case, this would be DAY, WEEK, MONTH, YEAR , zero means there is no limit. Max time less than 1 second will be equal to zero.

allProperties.nameKey: NiFi Flow-Fetch RDBMS Data-Minimum Time Unit

propertyDescriptor.name: Output Type
propertyDescriptor.description: How should the results be returned.  Either a Delimited output such as CSV, or AVRO.  If delimited you must specify the delimiter.

propertyDescriptor.name: Output Delimiter
propertyDescriptor.description: Used only if the Output Type is 'Delimited'.  If this is empty and the Output Type is delimited it will default to a ','.  This property is not used if the Output Type is AVRO.

table.feedFormat:
ROW FORMAT SERDE 'org.apache.hadoop.hive.serde2.OpenCSVSerde'
 WITH SERDEPROPERTIES ( 'separatorChar' = ',' ,'escapeChar' = '\\' ,'quoteChar' = '\"') STORED AS TEXTFILE
